    Dynegy introduces coal and emission products to Dynegydirect


 










 


















Dynegy introduces coal and emission products to Dynegydirect








03/26/2001









































HOUSTON, March 26, 2001 (PRNewswire) -- Dynegy Inc. (NYSE: DYN) today announced the expansion of Dynegydirect to include coal and emission products.Dynegydirect is an Internet-based, commission-free business-to-business portal and trading site for energy and communications commodities.  Since trading began in November 2000, Dynegydirect has recorded more than $9 billion in notional transactions and currently offers more than 500 products.In addition to natural gas, power, and natural gas liquids, Dynegydirect now offers three coal products and one emission product.  The coal products include Powder River Basin 8400 and 8800 and NYMEX spec.  Dynegydirect is also offering sulfur dioxide (SO2) emission allowances."Offering coal and emission products is a natural extension of the Dynegydirect platform," said Matt Schatzman, president of Energy Trading for Dynegy Inc.  "As we continue to grow, we will add new products and expand the services offered through Dynegydirect to meet the needs of our customers."Coal markets will be available from several supply regions, including the Southern Powder River Basin and Central Appalachia, with the initial delivery period of July 2001 and extending 18 months.  As the coal markets continue to evolve, additional eastern and western rail locations are expected to be added to Dynegydirect.  Dynegy is also offering spot markets for current vintage Environmental Protection Agency SO2 allowances.Dynegydirect provides customers with real-time access to prices for natural gas, power, natural gas liquids, coal and emission allowances in North America.  Dynegy customers and new users can view some of Dynegydirect's features by visiting http://www.dynegydirect.com, and interested parties may also register online.[Native Advertisement]Dynegy Inc. is a provider of energy and communications solutions to customers in North America, the United Kingdom and Continental Europe.  The company's leadership position extends across the entire convergence value chain, from power generation and wholesale and direct commercial and industrial marketing and trading of power, natural gas, coal, emission allowances, weather derivatives and broadband to transportation, gathering and processing of natural gas liquids.










 
























































